A list of members of the [[French Resistance (Earth-616)]].

__TOC__

==Members==
===Anna===
{| class="article-table"
|[[File:Anna (Earth-616) from Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1 0001.jpg|150px]]
|'''Appearances:''' {{c|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}

Anna, with the complicity of [[Margaret Carter (Earth-616)|Peggy Carter]] and [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]], managed to appropriate a German plane and with it bring the plans stolen from the Nazis to the Allied Forces.{{r|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}
|}

===Francois===
{| class="article-table"
|[[File:Francois (Earth-616) from Tales of Suspense Vol 1 77 0001.jpg|150px]]
|'''Appearances:''' {{c|Tales of Suspense Vol 1 77}}

During the liberation of [[Paris (France)|Paris]], [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]] sought Francois to be told where [[Margaret Carter (Earth-616)|Peggy Carter]] was, and Francois replied that she had been captured by the [[Geheime Staatspolizei (Earth-616)|Gestapo]] and that they had repeatedly tried to free her but to no avail.{{r|Tales of Suspense Vol 1 77}}
|}

===Henri===
{| class="article-table"
|[[File:Henri (Earth-616) from Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1 0001.jpg|150px]]
|'''Appearances:''' {{c|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}

Henri welcomed [[Margaret Carter (Earth-616)|Peggy Carter]] into the hideout of the Resistance and asked her if she had managed to get in touch with [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]].{{r|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}
|}

===Joan===
{| class="article-table"
|[[File:Joan (French Resistance) (Earth-616) from Captain America Comics Vol 1 32 0001.jpg|150px]]
|'''Appearances:''' {{c|Captain America Comics Vol 1 32}}

Joan was a member of the French Resistance who, with the help of [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]], did her best to save her brother Jacques, but when she discovered that her brother was a traitor and a spy for the [[National Socialist German Workers Party (Earth-616)|Nazis]], she killed him.{{r|Captain America Comics Vol 1 32}}
|}

===Marc===
{| class="article-table"
|[[File:Marc (Earth-616) from Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1 0001.jpg|150px]]
|'''Appearances:''' {{c|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}

Marc had infiltrated the ranks of the German army and managed to steal the plans of the Nazis and a Thermal Ray which he handed over to [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]].{{r|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}
|}

===Raoul===
{| class="article-table"
|[[File:Raoul (Earth-616) from Captain America Comics Vol 1 36 0001.jpg|150px]]
|'''Appearances:''' {{c|Captain America Comics Vol 1 36}} 

Raoul was a member of the [[French Resistance (Earth-616)|French Resistance]] who passed on information about the movements of German troops to allied forces.{{r|Captain America Comics Vol 1 36}}
|}

===Serge===
{| class="article-table"
|[[File:Serge (Earth-616) from Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1 0001.jpg|150px]]
|'''Appearances:''' {{c|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}

After joking around a bit, Serge asks [[Margaret Carter (Earth-616)|Peggy Carter]] if the meeting with [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]] is still taking place.{{r|Captain America and the First Thirteen Vol 1 1}}
|}

